<h4 class='bluish'>As Unordered Lists:</h4>
<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-xs-7 col-xs-offset-1">
		
		List groups allow for way to style HTML lists with bootstrap. It is list 
		group could be an unordered list with the class list-group where each item 
		has the class list-group-item. In Sublime Text type 
		ul.list-group>li.list-group-item{Item $}*4 and hit tab.<br>
		
	</div><div class="col-xs-4"></div>
</div>
<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-xs-4 black-text">
		<br>
		<ul class="list-group">
			<li class="list-group-item">Item 1</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">Item 2</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">Item 3</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">Item 4</li>
		</ul>
		
	</div>
	<div class="col-xs-8">
		<xmp>
			
<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">Item 1</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Item 2</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Item 3</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Item 4</li>
</ul>
			
		</xmp>
	</div>
</div>

<h4 class='bluish'>As Divs Containing Links:</h4>
<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-xs-7 col-xs-offset-1">
		
		You can also use a div with anchor tags instead of ul with li, respectively. 
		Make one list-group-item active by adding the class active. Bootstrap 
		colors can be added with the class list-group-item-XYZ where XYZ could be 
		success, info, warning or danger.
		<br>
		
	</div><div class="col-xs-4"></div>
</div>
<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-xs-4 black-text">
		<br>
		<div class='list-group'>
			<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-success active">Item 1</a>
			<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-info">Item 2</a>
			<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-warning">Item 3</a>
			<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-danger">Item 4</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="col-xs-8">
		<xmp>
			
<div class='list-group'>
	<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-success active">Item 1</a>
	<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-info">Item 2</a>
	<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-warning">Item 3</a>
	<a class="list-group-item list-group-item-danger">Item 4</a>
</div>
			
		</xmp>
	</div>
</div>	

<h4 class='bluish'>With Custom Content:</h4>
<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-xs-7 col-xs-offset-1">
		
		You aren't limited to just li's and a' in a list group. You can have 
		headers with the class list-group-item-heading and text with the class 
		list-group-item-heading:
		
	</div><div class="col-xs-4 black-text"></div>
</div>
<div class='row'>
